{"id":2493,"date":"2021-11-06T08:33:44","date_gmt":"2021-11-06T15:33:44","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/?p=2493"},"modified":"2021-11-06T08:33:44","modified_gmt":"2021-11-06T15:33:44","slug":"time-to-prepare-for-carm","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/blog\/time-to-prepare-for-carm\/","title":{"rendered":"Time to prepare for CARM"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Let\u2019s talk CARM!<\/p>\n<h2>First of all &#8211; what is it?<\/h2>\n<p>It\u2019s the modernization of the Canada Customs collections process.<\/p>\n<p><em>Before:<\/em><br \/>\nImporters paid private companies (customs brokers) for their duties &amp; taxes.<\/p>\n<p><em>After:<\/em><br \/>\nImporters will pay the government directly for duties &amp; taxes just like you do for your income tax.<\/p>\n<p>\u201cThe Canada Border Services Agency (CBSA) Assessment and Revenue Management (CARM) project is a multi-year initiative that will transform the collection of duties and taxes for goods imported into Canada.\u201d<\/p>\n<h2>How does CARM impact you as an importer?<\/h2>\n<p>Any company importing goods into Canada must register in the CCP and post financial security by May 2022.<\/p>\n<h2>When does CARM impact you as an importer?<\/h2>\n<p>CARM impacts your company now. The online CCP is currently available to register your company, delegate access and permissions, view account information, apply for advanced customs rulings, and make electronic payments directly to CBSA for duties and taxes. Rather than submitting payment to customs brokers, which will be a discontinued practice by May 2022, the online CCP will be the sole platform to communicate with the CBSA and make payments.<\/p>\n<p>Below is a step-by-step guide that you can use to register for CARM:<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 1:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Locate your Company Business Number<br \/>\nIt\u2019s 9 characters and looks like \u2018123456789RM0001\u2019<br \/>\nNote you need to have an RM \/ Importer Business Number<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 2:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Visit the CARM Portal<\/p>\n<p>https:\/\/ccp-pcc.cbsa-asfc.cloud-nuage.canada.ca\/en\/auth\/login<\/p>\n<p>Or Google \u201cCBSA CARM Portal\u201d<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 3:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Choose Your Sign In Partner<\/p>\n<p>This is just for verification &#8211; you can use your personal account<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 4:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Create Your Personal Profile<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 5:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Choose Register my Business<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 6:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Enter Your Company Business Number<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 7:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Validate Your Business Information<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 8:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Review Your Business Information<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 9:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>You\u2019re In!<br \/>\nCongratulations!<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 10:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Click \u201cSetup my portal\u201d<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 11:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Manage by business relationships<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 12:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Go to Received requests<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 13:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Click Approve on your Customs Broker<br \/>\n*If you do not see your broker in \u201cReceived requests\u201d contact your broker with your BN and ask them to send you a request through the CARM portal<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 14:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Select access to Specific Programs and then Program Management Access<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 15:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Preview and Approve access details<\/p>\n<p><strong>Step 16:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>You\u2019re Done!<br \/>\nYour Customs Broker is Active<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>If you have questions &#8211; we are here for you.<\/p>\n<p>Reach out to your existing contact at BorderBuddy or<a href=\"https:\/\/borderbuddy.com\/contact\/\"> contact us here<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Let\u2019s talk CARM! First of all &#8211; what is it? It\u2019s the modernization of the Canada Customs collections process. Before: Imp